  "text": "In Figure 5 we plot wages as a function of actual work experience. We applied a robust non-linear smoothing technique. At entry into first employment a considerable differential in wages is observed. [CITATION_1] Thereafter, wage experience profiles for men and women are slightly concavely shaped and seem to develop in almost [CITATION_2] What is not shown here is that before entry into first employment -that is while workers are in apprenticeship training and while they earn only approximately 30 percent of skilled workers' wages -the mean wages are very similar for males and females. parallel fashion. The differential, accordingly, stays almost constant during this period at around 0.25.",
